SO WHY EVEN HAVE IT
IN THE FIRST PLACE

04:50.023 --> 04:51.759
IF PEOPLE DON'T WANT TO BE
WITH EACH OTHER?

04:51.859 --> 04:55.128
I DON'T THINK THAT'S WHY.
IT'S JUST NOT DONE.

04:55.228 --> 04:56.864
WHAT'S THE DOWNSIDE
OF TELLING ME?

04:56.964 --> 04:59.633
I DON'T KNOW THAT
THERE IS A DOWNSIDE,
EXCEPT THAT--

04:59.733 --> 05:01.502
- YOU DON'T NEED TO KNOW.
- WHO'S COMING?

05:01.602 --> 05:03.404
- DON'T YOU DARE TELL HIM.
- WHAT'S THAT?

05:03.504 --> 05:05.005
- WHO'S COMING?
- I DON'T KNOW.

05:05.105 --> 05:08.376
WHY DO YOU EVEN GET STARTED
WITH HER ON THIS STUFF?

05:08.476 --> 05:10.310
- THAT'S MY QUESTION.
- WHAT TIME?

05:10.411 --> 05:12.112
- 7:30.
- YOU'VE GOT SOMETHING TO DO.

05:12.212 --> 05:14.448
- YOU'D BETTER GO DO IT.
- NOT NOW, MAYBE TONIGHT.

05:14.548 --> 05:16.350
- ALL RIGHT.
- THANK YOU.
SEE YOU LATER.

05:16.450 --> 05:19.252
CAN'T WAIT TO SEE YA!

05:19.353 --> 05:22.089
- YOU TAKE CARE
OF YOURSELF, ALL RIGHT?
- THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

05:22.189 --> 05:24.958
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
- WE STILL DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

05:25.058 --> 05:27.160
OH.
HI.

05:27.260 --> 05:31.298
OH SHOOT!
I FORGOT-- I GOTTA
FEED THOSE FISH AGAIN.

05:31.399 --> 05:33.734
IT'S LIKE A HUGE
RESPONSIBILITY--
FEEDING FISH.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.903
IT'S NOT FUN.
THINK ABOUT IT, YOU KNOW?

05:36.003 --> 05:38.338
I'M OUTSIDE, I GOTTA
GO HOME AND FEED FISH?

05:38.439 --> 05:40.674
I MEAN, SERIOUSLY,
WHO GIVES A SHIT?

05:40.774 --> 05:44.344
MR. DAVID, I WANTED
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT
YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

05:44.445 --> 05:46.213
YOU KNOW, THEY'RE
NOT PETS, REALLY.

05:46.313 --> 05:48.716
BUT YET IT'S THE SAME
RESPONSIBILITY AS A PET,

05:48.816 --> 05:50.718
BUT YOU GET NOTHING BACK.
YOU WATCH THEM,

05:50.818 --> 05:52.920
IS THAT SUPPOSED
TO BE FASCINATING?

05:53.020 --> 05:54.688
I DON'T KNOW.
UM...

05:54.788 --> 05:57.591
- CAN I TALK
TO YOU ABOUT LORETTA?
- WHAT DO YOU THINK?

05:57.691 --> 05:59.860
- WELL--
- DO YOU THINK SHE HAS--

05:59.960 --> 06:02.796
THINK SHE HAS CANCER?

06:02.896 --> 06:05.466
I-- I CAN'T SPECULATE
ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

06:05.566 --> 06:07.935
WE DID A BIOPSY
AT THE HOSPITAL AND--

06:08.035 --> 06:13.173
LET ME ASK YOU A QUESTION:
SAY YOU HAD TO MAKE A BET
WITH VEGAS ON THIS,

06:13.273 --> 06:16.944
WOULD YOU BET FOR CANCER
OR AGAINST CANCER?

06:17.044 --> 06:19.513
I-- I-- I DON'T GET
INTO THAT NUMBERS GAME.

06:19.613 --> 06:22.583
- YOU MUST HAVE AN IDEA.
- I DON'T.

06:22.683 --> 06:23.951
- NO IDEA?
- NO IDEA.

06:24.051 --> 06:26.587
WHAT IS THIS THING?
I'VE HAD THIS AWHILE.

06:26.687 --> 06:29.222
- WHAT IS THAT?
- IT'S JUST A SKIN TAG.

06:29.322 --> 06:30.891
JUST PUT A LITTLE LOTION
ON THERE.

06:30.991 --> 06:32.893
BUT-- HOLD ON A SEC.

06:32.993 --> 06:36.063
I'M GONNA WRITE YOU A FEW
PRESCRIPTIONS TO FILL OUT.

06:42.636 --> 06:46.373
I'M GONNA PRESCRIBE ZITHROMAX
AND TYLENOL WITH CODEINE.

06:46.474 --> 06:49.342
NOW THE TYLENOL,
THAT'S JUST AS NEEDED
FOR PAIN.

06:49.443 --> 06:52.946
AGAIN, IN A FEW DAYS--
ANY DAY,

06:53.046 --> 06:55.816
WE'LL HAVE THE BIOPSY BACK
AND THAT WILL

06:55.916 --> 06:58.418
HELP US DETERMINE
WHAT THE NEXT STEP IS.

06:58.519 --> 07:00.821
BUT RIGHT NOW, I WANT YOU
TO JUST STAY CALM,

07:00.921 --> 07:03.323
AND-- WHAT'S WRONG?

07:03.423 --> 07:05.258
( snorts )
YOU JUST

07:05.358 --> 07:08.929
GO INTO THE REFRIGERATOR
WITHOUT ASKING?

07:09.029 --> 07:11.298
I JUST GOT MYSELF
A LEMONADE.
IS THAT A--

07:11.398 --> 07:13.701
I WAS JUST SURPRISED
YOU DIDN'T ASK.

07:13.801 --> 07:17.104
- I'M SURPRISED YOU
DIDN'T OFFER, TO BE HONEST.
- WELL, I WAS ABOUT TO OFFER.

07:17.204 --> 07:19.973
- I DON'T THINK
YOU WERE ABOUT TO OFFER...
- WELL, I WAS GONNA OFFER--

07:20.073 --> 07:22.710
- ...IF YOU HADN'T
OFFERED ME BY NOW.
- IT IS A LITTLE UNUSUAL

07:22.810 --> 07:25.579
TO GO INTO
SOMEONE'S REFRIGERATOR
WITHOUT ASKING, IS IT NOT?

07:25.679 --> 07:29.216
I CAN TELL WHEN SOMEBODY'S GONNA
OFFER ME LEMONADE. YOU WERE NOT
GOING TO OFFER ME LEMONADE.

07:29.316 --> 07:32.052
IF ANYTHING, YOU WERE GOING
TO COMPLAIN TO ME ABOUT BEING
A FISH OWNER OR SOMETHING.

07:32.152 --> 07:34.888
- IT IS DIFFICULT
TO BE A FISH OWNER.
- WHY IS THAT A PRIORITY?!

07:34.988 --> 07:37.658
- YOUR GIRLFRIEND IS SICK.
- I DIDN'T SAY IT'S A PRIORITY.

07:37.758 --> 07:41.161
I JUST SAID THAT THEY NEED
TO BE FED AND IT'S SOMETHING
THAT I NEED TO THINK ABOUT.

07:41.261 --> 07:42.696
YOU DO NOT NEED
TO THINK ABOUT THAT.

07:42.796 --> 07:44.965
WHAT YOU NEED TO THINK ABOUT
IS THE SICK WOMAN UPSTAIRS.

07:45.065 --> 07:47.134
I'M THINKING ABOUT THAT.
AND BY THE WAY,
WHY COULDN'T YOU ASK?

07:47.234 --> 07:49.069
- WHY COULDN'T--
- ARE YOU SO DAINTY
YOU CAN'T SAY

07:49.169 --> 07:51.805
- "MAY I PLEASE HAVE
A GLASS OF WATER?"
- I AM NOT DAINTY!

07:51.905 --> 07:54.474
"MAY I HAVE A PIECE OF PIE?"
IT COULD BE TUNA FISH--
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

07:54.575 --> 07:55.709
- YOU KNOW.
- NO, IT DOES MATTER.

07:55.809 --> 07:57.878
HERE, YOU WANT?
TAKE-- TAKE THIS.

07:57.978 --> 08:00.614
- YOU DON'T OFFER-- A HOT DAY--
A MOVER COMES HERE...
- YOU WANT THIS?

08:00.714 --> 08:03.684
- ...YOU SAY,
"YOU WANT SOME TUNA FISH?"
- YOU WANT THIS LITTLE PEAR?

08:03.784 --> 08:05.619
DON'T CONDESCEND TO ME
WITH YOUR TINY PEAR.

08:05.719 --> 08:08.088
I'M NOT THE ONE
THAT HAS A PROBLEM HERE.
YOU ARE, MY FRIEND.

08:08.188 --> 08:10.223
- YOU ARE.
- YEAH.

08:10.323 --> 08:11.625
- OKAY, FINE.
- YEAH, FINE.

08:11.725 --> 08:13.561
- HEY, DR. SCHAFFER.
- HELLO.

08:13.661 --> 08:15.696
DID YOU SEE THAT?
DID YOU SEE THAT GUY?

08:15.796 --> 08:17.798
- WHAT WAS THAT WHOLE THING?
- HE GOES IN MY REFRIGERATOR.

08:17.898 --> 08:19.432
- COME ON, YOU DON'T DO THAT.
- WHAT DID HE TAKE?

08:19.533 --> 08:21.769
- LEMONADE.
- LIQUIDS ARE OKAY.

08:21.869 --> 08:25.072
I DON'T BELIEVE THAT PEOPLE
SHOULD GO INTO MY REFRIGERATOR.

08:25.172 --> 08:27.440
- WHAT KIND OF
A STUPID RULE THIS THAT?
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

08:27.541 --> 08:29.309
I DON'T GO INTO OTHER
PEOPLE'S REFRIGERATORS.

08:29.409 --> 08:30.944
YOU COULD GO
INTO MY REFRIGERATOR.

08:31.044 --> 08:33.581
- I DON'T GO
INTO YOUR REFRIGERATOR.
- YOU'RE A WELCOME GUEST.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.248
HEY, HOW'S YOUR SISTER,
BY THE WAY?

08:35.348 --> 08:36.917
- BAM BAM?
- YEAH.

08:37.017 --> 08:39.019
- THANKS FOR ASKING.
SHE'S DOING A LOT BETTER.
- REALLY?

08:39.119 --> 08:42.255
YEAH. I'M REALLY GLAD
WE TOOK HER OUT OF THAT
MENTAL INSTITUTION.

08:42.355 --> 08:43.657
- THAT'S GOOD.
- YEAH, I'M EXCITED.

08:43.757 --> 08:46.459
YOU KNOW, IF THERE'S
ANYTHING I CAN DO--

08:46.560 --> 08:48.796
YOU LET ME KNOW.

08:48.896 --> 08:52.299
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THERE IS SOMETHING YOU CAN DO.

08:52.399 --> 08:54.434
- WHAT?
- YEAH, YOU CAN COME OVER

08:54.534 --> 08:57.204
TODAY AT 1:00
AND VISIT WITH HER.

08:57.304 --> 08:59.607
- VISIT HER?
WHAT, ARE YOU KIDDING?
- YEAH.

08:59.707 --> 09:02.209
- WHY, YOU DIDN'T MEAN IT?
- OF COURSE NOT!

09:02.309 --> 09:03.877
WHY DID YOU SAY IT THEN?

09:03.977 --> 09:06.079
YOU KNOW, IT WAS SOME--
AN EMPTY GESTURE.

09:06.179 --> 09:08.248
- IT WAS SOMETHING TO SAY.
- GUESS WHAT.

09:08.348 --> 09:11.318
YOU SAID IT.
BE THERE AT 1:00.

09:11.418 --> 09:13.854
BUT ONE THING-- WHEN YOU
GO IN THE HOUSE,

09:13.954 --> 09:16.724
LOOK AT HER SHOES BEFORE
SHE CALLS YOUR NAME.

09:16.824 --> 09:19.192
DON'T LOOK
AT HER IN THE EYES.
SHE'D LOVE TO SEE YOU.

09:19.292 --> 09:23.196
OH, CHRIST.
I DON'T KNOW HOW YOU TAKE
A STATEMENT LIKE THAT SERIOUSLY.

09:23.296 --> 09:25.532
BUT YOU SAID IT
AND YOU'RE GONNA STICK TO IT.

09:25.633 --> 09:27.668
- AND MAKE HER FEEL GOOD!
- ALL RIGHT.

09:27.768 --> 09:29.670
I'LL SEE YOU
AT JEFF'S TONIGHT.

09:32.139 --> 09:33.907
WHAT'S AT JEFF'S?

09:34.007 --> 09:36.644
OH.

09:37.845 --> 09:40.013
OH, HE'S, UM,
HAVING A LITTLE...

09:41.148 --> 09:43.150
DINNER PARTY.

09:43.250 --> 09:45.418
I GUESS I WASN'T INVITED.

09:45.518 --> 09:47.587
I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT.

09:47.688 --> 09:52.059
WHY DON'T YOU MAKE SURE
BEFORE YOU ASK SOMEBODY,
"AM I GONNA SEE YOU TONIGHT?"

09:52.159 --> 09:54.461
- THAT THEY WERE INVITED?
- I JUST ASSUMED YOU WERE GOING.

09:54.561 --> 09:56.630
- DON'T ASSUME ANYTHING.
- IF THEY HAD TOLD ME

09:56.730 --> 09:59.132
WHO WAS COMING TO THE PARTY,
I WOULD HAVE KNOWN

09:59.232 --> 10:02.402
- AND I WOULDN'T HAVE ASKED,
BUT THEY REFUSED TO TELL ME.
- IT'S NOT YOUR JOB

10:02.502 --> 10:04.437
TO FIND OUT
WHO'S GOING TO A PARTY.

10:04.537 --> 10:07.808
ALL I WANT YOU TO DO
IS ENTERTAIN MY SISTER
FOR TWO HOURS

10:07.908 --> 10:10.077
AND THEN YOU CAN GO
TO YOUR GODDAMN DINNER PARTY.

10:10.177 --> 10:12.680
- SHE BETTER NOT BE DANGEROUS.
- BE THERE AT 1:00, OKAY?

10:12.780 --> 10:15.348
I'LL BE THERE!
I GOTTA SIT IN A ROOM
WITH THAT NUT?

10:30.497 --> 10:32.900
- YOU LOOK GOOD.
- YOU DO.

10:33.000 --> 10:34.467
- THANK YOU.
- MM-HMM.

10:34.567 --> 10:36.636
THANK YOU, JEFF.

10:36.737 --> 10:38.939
AND I APPRECIATE
THE EFFORT, LARRY.

10:39.039 --> 10:41.208
- NO EFFORT.
- NO, IT WAS EFFORTLESS.

10:41.308 --> 10:43.844
OKAY, THEN WE'RE ALL HAPPY.

10:43.944 --> 10:45.645
YEAH.

10:48.015 --> 10:51.518
SO WHAT'S NEW?
( laughs ) RIGHT?

10:51.618 --> 10:53.486
SO WHAT'S HAPPENING?

10:53.586 --> 10:56.957
( laughs )
GUESS WHO TOLD
MARTY TO SHUT UP.

10:57.057 --> 10:58.992
- I GIVE UP.
- WHY, WHAT DID HE SAY? WHO?

10:59.092 --> 11:01.061
- HE DIDN'T TELL YOU?
OH, COME ON.
- Larry: NO NO.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.830
SHE'S GREAT--
A GREAT ACTRESS.

11:02.930 --> 11:04.898
- ANGELINA JOLIE?
- NO!

11:04.998 --> 11:07.334
YOU KNOW WHO I MEAN.
SHE'S AN ACTRESS.

11:07.434 --> 11:09.870
- WHO WHO?
- SHE SAID SHUT UP
RIGHT TO MARTY.

11:09.970 --> 11:11.571
- NICOLE KIDMAN?
- NO!

11:11.671 --> 11:13.040
- JULIA ROBERTS?
- NO!

11:13.140 --> 11:16.509
SHE'S A MULTI--
MULTI-TALENTED.

11:16.609 --> 11:18.345
OH, I KNOW, I KNOW!
HANNAH MONTANA.

11:18.445 --> 11:20.547
- NO, YOU'RE NOT EVEN TRYING!
- I'M TRYING!

11:20.647 --> 11:22.816
- THE KARDASHIANS!
- WHAT?

11:22.916 --> 11:25.185
NO! YOU KNOW
WHO IT IS!

11:27.520 --> 11:29.389
- DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA?
- NO.

11:29.489 --> 11:31.725
YEAH, YOU DO.

11:38.131 --> 11:41.468
( singing obscure jingles )

11:52.846 --> 11:54.681
GOT ANYTHING TO EAT?

11:54.782 --> 11:56.850
- NO.
- ANYTHING TO DRINK?

11:56.950 --> 11:59.286
- NOPE.
- NOTHING TO EAT OR DRINK?

11:59.386 --> 12:02.522
- NO, I'M SORRY, NOTHING.
- BOY, THAT'S INTERESTING.

12:02.622 --> 12:04.825
I KNOW. REALLY.
ISN'T IT?

12:04.925 --> 12:07.127
IT IS.
I'M GONNA GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

12:07.227 --> 12:09.062
I WAS GONNA GO
TO THE BATHROOM.
CAN I GO FIRST?

12:09.162 --> 12:10.898
I JUST SAID I'M GOING
TO THE BATHROOM.

12:10.998 --> 12:13.000
- BUT I'M SAYING,
COULD I GO FIRST?
- NO NO, I'M GOING FIRST.

12:13.100 --> 12:14.667
- SO WHEN YOU COME BACK,
I'M GONNA GO.
- YES.

12:14.768 --> 12:16.636
OKAY.

12:16.736 --> 12:18.806
YEAH.

12:49.369 --> 12:51.338
( thumping, moaning )

12:54.975 --> 12:56.844
( Bam Bam moaning )

12:59.779 --> 13:03.083
- ( Jeff panting )
- Bam Bam: HEY HEY HEY!

13:03.183 --> 13:06.186
HEY HEY!

13:06.286 --> 13:08.388
HEY HEY HEY HEY!

13:08.488 --> 13:10.757
( moans )
OH HEY!

13:10.858 --> 13:13.894
OH, FUCK ME, FAT BOY!

13:15.362 --> 13:18.365
FUCK ME, FAT BOY!

13:18.465 --> 13:20.633
- SHE'S NOT A MENTAL PATIENT.
- YOU HAD SEX WITH
A MENTAL PATIENT!

13:20.733 --> 13:22.970
- SHE'S NOT A MENTAL PATIENT.
- SHE'S A MENTAL PATIENT.

13:23.070 --> 13:24.872
- SHE'S LIVING AT FUNKHOUSER'S.
- SHE'S A MENTAL PATIENT.

13:24.972 --> 13:27.841
IF I WENT OVER TO THE
INSTITUTION AND FUCKED HER,
THEN SHE'S A MENTAL PATIENT.

13:27.941 --> 13:29.843
WHAT HAPPENED?
I GOT UP TO GO TO THE BATHROOM.

13:29.943 --> 13:32.812
I WAS SITTING THERE
AND SHE SAID, "I'M BORED."

13:32.913 --> 13:35.048
I SAID, "IF THERE'S
ANYTHING I CAN DO"--

13:35.148 --> 13:36.416
- YOU SAID THAT?
- THAT'S IT.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.451
- AN EMPTY GESTURE?
- AN EMPTY GESTURE.

13:38.551 --> 13:40.854
- THAT'S HOW THIS
WHOLE THING STARTED.
- THAT'S HOW IT STARTED

13:40.954 --> 13:42.990
- AND THEN I'M OFF
BANGING HER.
- JESUS.

13:43.090 --> 13:44.958
YOU CAN'T MAKE
AN EMPTY GESTURE
TO A FUNKHOUSER.

13:45.058 --> 13:47.327
THEY TAKE YOU UP ON IT.

13:51.932 --> 13:54.868
HOW COME YOU DON'T
HAVE A DOORBELL?

13:54.968 --> 13:57.137
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DID?
YOU TOTALLY FUCKED ME.

13:57.237 --> 13:59.306
- WHAT?
- YOU FUCKED ME.

13:59.406 --> 14:01.942
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- WHAT'D YOU TELL FUNKHOUSER
ABOUT THE PARTY FOR?

14:02.042 --> 14:03.610
PFFT, OH, WHY?
HE SAID SOMETHING?

14:03.710 --> 14:06.179
YEAH, HE SAID SOMETHING.
HE CALLED TO COMPLAIN
HE WASN'T INVITED

14:06.279 --> 14:09.016
- AND SUSIE INVITED HIM.
- OH, THAT IS SO LAME!
YOU KNOW THAT?

14:09.116 --> 14:12.219
- THAT IS SO LAME
TO CALL UP AND DO THAT.
- AND GUESS WHAT ELSE THEY DID.

14:12.319 --> 14:17.424
THEY BROUGHT BAM BAM.
BAM BAM'S HERE!

14:17.524 --> 14:20.527
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- HE BROUGHT THAT FUCKING
NUTBAG INTO MY HOUSE!

14:20.627 --> 14:23.496
- OH MY GOD.
- WHAT THE FUCK DID YOU
GO AND TELL HIM FOR?

14:23.596 --> 14:26.166
IF YOU HAD TOLD ME
WHO WAS COMING TO THE PARTY
IN THE FIRST PLACE,

14:26.266 --> 14:29.702
I NEVER WOULD HAVE SAID ANYTHING
TO HIM BECAUSE I WOULD HAVE
KNOWN HE WASN'T COMING.

14:29.802 --> 14:32.940
IT'S CRAZY-- ALL THESE
PARTY RULES: YOU CAN'T
TELL WHO YOU'RE INVITING,

14:33.040 --> 14:34.607
YOU CAN'T TELL ANYBODY
YOU'RE GOING

14:34.707 --> 14:36.143
AND YOU CAN'T TALK
ABOUT IT AFTER.

14:36.243 --> 14:38.245
IT'S LIKE LIVING
IN EAST GERMANY
OR SOMETHING.

14:38.345 --> 14:40.713
NOW I'M SCREWED.
JUST LOOK AT THIS.

14:40.813 --> 14:42.449
- THIS IS CRAZY.
- WHAT IS THAT?

14:42.549 --> 14:44.851
IS THAT DR. SCHAFFER?
WHAT'S HE DOING HERE?

14:44.952 --> 14:47.220
HE HAD A PARTY RECENTLY.
HE INVITED US.
WE'RE RETURNING THE FAVOR.

14:47.320 --> 14:49.189
- WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?
- AGAIN.

14:49.289 --> 14:51.858
- AGAIN WHAT?
- IF I HAD KNOWN THAT
HE WAS GONNA BE HERE,

14:51.959 --> 14:54.962
- I WOULDN'T HAVE COME.
- IF I HAD KNOWN BAM BAM
WAS GONNA BE HERE,

14:55.062 --> 14:58.698
I WOULD HAVE LEFT TOWN!

14:58.798 --> 15:01.268
- WHO'S THAT GUY
WITH THE DOCTOR?
- THAT'S HIS BOYFRIEND.

15:01.368 --> 15:03.503
- WHAT, SERIOUSLY?
- YEAH, HE'S GAY.

15:03.603 --> 15:06.739
- OH MY GOD, I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.
- YEAH, LISTEN, I GOTTA
GO HELP SUSIE.

15:06.839 --> 15:08.341
OKAY.
HEY, HOW YOU DOING?

15:08.441 --> 15:10.377
- HI, MR. DAVID,
HOW ARE YOU?
- GOOD.

15:10.477 --> 15:12.245
- THIS IS SAM.
- HI. IT'S GOOD TO MEET YOU.

15:12.345 --> 15:14.081
NICE TO MEET YOU.
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE GAY.

15:14.181 --> 15:16.984
UH, YEAH.
IS THAT A SURPRISE TO YOU?

15:17.084 --> 15:18.818
YEAH, I'M A LITTLE
SURPRISED, YEAH.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.720
- WHY?
- I DON'T KNOW.

15:20.820 --> 15:23.723
- I JUST DIDN'T
THINK YOU WERE GAY.
- WHAT IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

15:23.823 --> 15:26.994
IT DOESN'T MEAN ANYTHING.
IT MEANS I WAS SURPRISED
TO DISCOVER THAT HE'S GAY.

15:27.094 --> 15:29.896
- THAT'S WHAT IT MEANS.
- BUT WHY? HOW WOULD I SEEM
IF I WAS GAY?

15:29.997 --> 15:32.832
- WHAT IS SEEMING GAY?
- YOU SEEM SLIGHTLY GAY
AND YOU DON'T.

15:32.932 --> 15:36.569
- SO I WOULDN'T BE SURPRISED
IF SOMEBODY TOLD ME--
- OH REALLY?

15:36.669 --> 15:38.972
--BUT I'M SURPRISED
THAT SOMEBODY TELLS ME
YOU'RE GAY.

15:39.072 --> 15:40.740
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
IS THAT A CRIME?

15:40.840 --> 15:42.875
- NO, IT'S NOT A CRIME.
IT'S JUST ODD.
- IT'S NOT A CRIME.

15:42.976 --> 15:45.445
- AND IT'S
A LITTLE BIT OFFENSIVE.
- I'M SORRY IF YOU'RE OFFENDED.

15:45.545 --> 15:48.315
- I DON'T THINK
I SAID ANYTHING OFFENSIVE.
- I DON'T ACCEPT YOUR APOLOGY

15:48.415 --> 15:50.217
'CAUSE I DON'T BELIEVE
THAT YOU ARE SORRY.

15:50.317 --> 15:51.985
HOW ABOUT IF I SAID
I'M PLEASANTLY SURPRISED?

15:52.085 --> 15:53.486
YOU'RE LIVING
IN ANOTHER DECADE,
MR. DAVID.

15:53.586 --> 15:55.922
- I DON'T THINK I AM.
- WELL, I THINK YOU ARE.

15:56.023 --> 15:57.390
- OKAY?
- ALL RIGHT, FINE.

15:57.490 --> 15:59.926
- FINE, WE DISAGREE.
- OKAY, WE'LL AGREE TO DISAGREE.

16:00.027 --> 16:01.394
ALL RIGHT, GREAT.

16:01.494 --> 16:03.163
UNBELIEVABLE.

16:03.263 --> 16:05.932
WHAT DID YOU DO
WITH BAM BAM?

16:06.033 --> 16:07.767
WHAT? NOTHING.
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

16:07.867 --> 16:10.570
- WHEN YOU CAME
OVER TO THE HOUSE.
- I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

16:10.670 --> 16:12.305
IT'S LIKE A MIRACLE.

16:12.405 --> 16:15.008
I'VE NEVER SEEN
HER SPIRITS LIKE THIS.

16:15.108 --> 16:17.510
I MEAN, THE MEDICINE
AND YOUR VISIT--

16:17.610 --> 16:20.613
- SHE'S A DIFFERENT PERSON.
- THAT IS FANTASTIC!

16:20.713 --> 16:22.515
- WHAT GREAT NEWS.
- I CAN'T THANK YOU ENOUGH.

16:22.615 --> 16:24.717
I-- YOU SHOULDN'T
BE GIVING ME ANY
OF THE CREDIT.

16:24.817 --> 16:26.786
- THIS IS THE MAN--
COME HERE, COME HERE.
- WHAT?

16:26.886 --> 16:29.656
- HE SAYS BAM BAM IS...
- SHHH!

16:29.756 --> 16:31.824
- ...IS LIKE A NEW PERSON.
- HOW ABOUT THAT?

16:31.924 --> 16:33.760
- THAT'S GREAT.
- WERE YOU THERE TOO?

16:33.860 --> 16:36.763
- YEAH!
- NO WONDER SHE WAS SINGING
"I LOVE THE FAT BOY."

16:36.863 --> 16:40.067
- I COULDN'T FIGURE IT OUT.
- I LOVE THE FAT BOY.

16:40.167 --> 16:41.901
- HOW ABOUT THAT?
- IT'S GREAT.

16:42.001 --> 16:43.636
I CAN'T THANK
YOU GUYS ENOUGH!

16:43.736 --> 16:45.105
- OH.
- PLEASURE.

16:45.205 --> 16:47.540
- WHAT DID YOU DO?
- WE JUST SAT AND TALKED
WITH HER.

16:47.640 --> 16:49.276
- THAT'S ALL.
- DID YOU PLAY ANY GAMES?

16:49.376 --> 16:51.178
- NO NO NO.
- I LAID SOME GAMES OUT.

16:51.278 --> 16:52.345
- NO.
- NO GAMES, UH-HUH.

16:52.445 --> 16:54.347
DID YOU PLAY A MILLION
PICK-UP STICKS?

16:54.447 --> 16:56.616
- Both: NO NO.
- THE KEY TO THE WHOLE THING?

16:56.716 --> 16:59.519
YOU TREAT THEM NORMAL
AND THEY REALLY RESPOND.

16:59.619 --> 17:03.223
I LOVE BOTH OF YOU
AND YOU GOTTA PROMISE ME
YOU'LL DO IT AGAIN.

17:03.323 --> 17:05.958
- IF WE HAVE TIME.
- IT'S POSSIBLE.

17:06.059 --> 17:07.594
OH NO,
YOU GOTTA PROMISE.

17:07.694 --> 17:09.762
- EHHH--
- WE'LL SEE.

17:09.862 --> 17:12.565
- JUST SAY YOU'LL GO OVER THERE.
- Susie: DINNER IS SERVED!

17:12.665 --> 17:15.702
- LET'S GO HAVE SOME DINNER.
- THANK YOU SO MUCH!

17:15.802 --> 17:18.271
- SO YOU'RE SAYING
THAT IT WORKS?
- ABSOLUTELY IT WORKS.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.440
- I DO IT EVERY DAY.
- AND, SAM, YOU'VE USED IT?

17:20.540 --> 17:23.676
- YOU MADE THE SALAD, RIGHT?
- I MADE IT AND I LOVE IT.

17:23.776 --> 17:25.945
( loudly clears throat )

17:26.045 --> 17:28.448
( all chattering )

18:07.454 --> 18:10.022
SUSIE, THESE INGREDIENTS
ARE VERY FRESH AND
WELL PREPARED.

18:10.123 --> 18:12.159
OH, THANK YOU, BAM BAM.
THAT'S SO SWEET OF YOU.

18:12.259 --> 18:14.461
I'M SO GLAD YOU WERE
ABLE TO JOIN US.

18:14.561 --> 18:16.863
I'M SO GLAD YOU STILL HAVE
FOOD IN YOUR FRIDGE

18:16.963 --> 18:19.232
- CONSIDERING LARRY'S AROUND.
- Susie: WHAT IS THAT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

18:19.332 --> 18:22.034
LARRY LIKES TO CLEAN OUT
FRIDGES LIKE HE DID TODAY
AT MARTY'S HOUSE.

18:22.135 --> 18:23.503
- WHAT?
- YOU WERE INTO OUR FRIDGE

18:23.603 --> 18:26.206
- UNINVITED, RIGHT?
- THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

18:26.306 --> 18:28.441
OH? THEN MIGHT YOU EXPLAIN
THE WHEREABOUTS

18:28.541 --> 18:30.977
OF THE FRESHLY-SLICED
DELI-PACKAGED TURKEY...

18:31.077 --> 18:34.181
- I DON'T EVEN EAT TURKEY.
- ...THE YELLOW MUSTARD
IN A GLASS JAR

18:34.281 --> 18:36.115
- AND THE LEMONADE SODA?
- WHAT?!

18:36.216 --> 18:38.418
OH, LEMONADE?
SO YOU'RE A HYPOCRITE TOO?

18:38.518 --> 18:40.753
BECAUSE I HAD LEMONADE
AT YOUR HOUSE AND YOU THREW--

18:40.853 --> 18:42.255
PARDON ME--
A SHIT FIT.

18:42.355 --> 18:44.791
ARE YOU KIDDING?
SHE'S EMOTIONALLY UNSTABLE.

18:44.891 --> 18:47.059
ARE YOU GONNA BELIEVE
A WORD THIS WOMAN SAYS?

18:47.160 --> 18:49.496
YOU KNOW, I DON'T MIND
IF YOU TAKE LIQUID,

18:49.596 --> 18:52.064
BUT WHEN YOU TAKE REGULAR FOOD,
I HAVE A PROBLEM.

18:52.165 --> 18:53.766
I DIDN'T TAKE ANYTHING!
THAT'S CRAZY.

18:53.866 --> 18:55.802
SPEAK THE TRUTH.
HELP HIM WITH THE TRUTH,
WOULD YOU, JEFF?

18:55.902 --> 18:58.638
I WOULDN'T KNOW.
I ACTUALLY WASN'T THERE
IN THE KITCHEN.

18:58.738 --> 19:01.374
YOU WERE-- YOU WERE-- OH NO,
YOU WEREN'T. I KNOW
WHERE YOU WERE!

19:01.474 --> 19:03.376
- YOU WERE IN BED WITH ME.
- Susie/Jeff: WHAT?

19:03.476 --> 19:05.678
- ( scoffs )
- COME ON.

19:05.778 --> 19:08.080
- Marty: WHAT DID YOU SAY?
- Susie: WHAT DID YOU SAY?

19:08.181 --> 19:10.950
WHAT THE FUCK IS
SHE TALKING ABOUT JEFF?
WHAT THE HELL DID YOU DO?

19:11.050 --> 19:13.119
- OH, I DID NOTHING.
- Larry: HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

19:13.220 --> 19:16.356
- DID YOU TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THIS POOR DERANGED GIRL?
- ( all shouting )

19:16.456 --> 19:19.526
- YOU ARE SICK!
- SHAME ON YOU.

19:19.626 --> 19:22.562
- THAT'S DISGUSTING.
- Susie: WHAT DID YOU DO NOW?

19:22.662 --> 19:24.897
- SERIOUSLY, HUH?
- Susie: YOU SICK
FUCKING PERVERT.

19:24.997 --> 19:28.167
YOU'RE-- YOU'RE SERVING
NOTHING BUT LIES HERE.
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

19:30.403 --> 19:32.405
- COME ON!
- WHAT DID YOU DO
TO HER, JEFFREY?

19:32.505 --> 19:34.974
- HOW COULD YOU DO THAT?
- SHE'S FUCKING NUTS!

19:35.074 --> 19:37.377
SHE'S A NUTBAG!
SHE'S A NUTBAG.

19:37.477 --> 19:40.247
- I DID NOT DO ANYTHING. CRAZY!
- HE'S GONNA SLEEP WITH
A MENTAL PATIENT?

19:40.347 --> 19:41.914
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT!

19:42.014 --> 19:43.716
I BELIEVE YOU!

19:43.816 --> 19:47.454
EVEN BAM BAM IS NOT
CRAZY ENOUGH TO SLEEP
WITH YOU, OKAY?

19:47.554 --> 19:49.656
- ONLY I AM.
- Jeff: THERE YOU GO.

19:49.756 --> 19:52.259
- THERE YOU GO.
- THAT'S EXACTLY--

19:52.359 --> 19:54.861
THAT'S EXACTLY RIGHT.
OF COURSE.

19:54.961 --> 19:56.663
OKAY, EVERYBODY,
EVERYBODY,

19:56.763 --> 20:00.267
I WANT TO APOLOGIZE
FOR THE FUNKHOUSER FAMILY.

20:00.367 --> 20:01.834
OH, STOP.
IT'S NOT NECESSARY.

20:01.934 --> 20:03.570
- NO NO.
- Jeff: NO NEED
TO APOLOGIZE.

20:03.670 --> 20:07.740
I'M GOING
TO HAVE TO TAKE HER BACK
TO THE INSTITUTION.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.976
I'M GONNA TELL YOU SOMETHING:
I THINK IT WOULD BE
GOOD FOR HER.

20:10.076 --> 20:12.645
AND YOU'RE DOING IT
FOR HER OWN SAFETY,
FOR HER OWN GOOD.

20:12.745 --> 20:14.414
- NO, I'M NOT SO CERTAIN.
- NO, IT'S GOOD.

20:14.514 --> 20:16.416
IT WOULD BE FANTASTIC.
IT'S A GREAT THING,

20:16.516 --> 20:18.651
BECAUSE YOU'VE GOTTA
THINK OF THE LONG HAUL.

20:18.751 --> 20:20.453
IN THE LONG HAUL,
YOU WANT HER BACK.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.522
- MAYBE SHE NEEDS HELP BACK.
- Susie: YOU WANT TO HELP HER.

20:22.622 --> 20:25.292
- LOOK LOOK LOOK, JUST DROP IT.
- ( cell phone ringing )

20:25.392 --> 20:27.460
LET'S ENJOY OUR DINNER.
I'M SORRY THIS HAPPENED.

20:27.560 --> 20:29.262
THE BEST SALAD
ANYBODY EVER MADE.

20:29.362 --> 20:31.964
- Susie: THANK YOU, SWEETHEART.
- HELLO?

20:32.064 --> 20:34.166
WHAT?
HOLD ON, HEY, WHAT?

20:34.267 --> 20:36.102
OH, OKAY.

20:36.202 --> 20:38.771
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL GO PICK IT UP.
NO, I'LL LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

20:38.871 --> 20:41.441
- Susie: YOU'RE LEAVING?
- I'M SO SORRY.

20:41.541 --> 20:43.776
I HAVE TO GO.
I HAVE TO PICK UP
LORETTA'S MEDICATION.

20:43.876 --> 20:46.913
- YOU DIDN'T GIVE IT TO HER YET?
- NO, I'VE GOTTA GET IT
FROM THE PHARMACY.

20:47.013 --> 20:49.649
- I'M SORRY, SHE'S SICK.
- YOU'RE LEAVING, I HAVEN'T
SERVED THE ENTREE YET.

20:49.749 --> 20:52.352
IT'S SAD BECAUSE I'M HAVING
SO MUCH FUN HERE, AND THEN--

20:52.452 --> 20:54.321
AND I GOTTA GO AND--
MAYBE I'LL COME BACK.

20:54.421 --> 20:56.022
NO, DON'T BOTHER
COMING BACK.

20:56.122 --> 20:57.790
GO GO GO!

21:00.760 --> 21:03.262
I GOT THE PRESCRIPTION,
AUNTIE RAE. I'M JUST GONNA
GET SOME FOOD TO GO.

21:03.363 --> 21:05.231
- COULD YOU DO ME A FAVOR?
- WHAT?

21:05.332 --> 21:08.501
COULD YOU GO UP TO LORETTA
AND ASK HER WHAT THE NAME
OF THAT RESTAURANT WAS

21:08.601 --> 21:10.337
WE ATE IN IN SANTA MONICA
A FEW WEEKS AGO?

21:10.437 --> 21:11.771
- NO.
- Why not?

21:11.871 --> 21:14.240
- Because she's resting.
- IS SHE SLEEPING?

21:14.341 --> 21:16.208
- NO.
- Can she talk?

21:16.309 --> 21:18.378
- YES.
- SO LET HER TALK.

21:18.478 --> 21:21.381
NO. I DON'T WANT HER TALKING.
I WANT HER RESTING.

21:21.481 --> 21:23.716
RESTING?
WHAT DOES RESTING EVEN MEAN?

21:23.816 --> 21:26.886
SHE'S NOT SLEEPING, IS SHE?
YOU CAN TALK AND REST.

21:26.986 --> 21:30.122
LARRY, I AM NOT GONNA BOTHER
LORETTA WITH THIS BULLSHIT.
DO YOU HEAR ME?

21:30.222 --> 21:32.325
SHE RESTING.
BYE.

21:37.029 --> 21:39.466
- HI.
- OH, HI, MR. DAVID.
NICE TO SEE YOU.

21:39.566 --> 21:42.602
- I'D LIKE SOME FOOD TO GO.
- OH, I JUST SAT YOUR PARTY.

21:42.702 --> 21:45.304
- PARTY?
- YEAH, YOU HAD A RESERVATION.

21:45.405 --> 21:47.073
I HAVE A RESERVATION?
LET ME SEE.

21:47.173 --> 21:49.576
"LARRY DAVID, 2."

21:50.810 --> 21:52.945
MY GOD.

21:53.045 --> 21:55.382
THANK YOU.

21:56.883 --> 21:59.285
WELL WELL.

21:59.386 --> 22:02.389
- HI, LARRY.
- HI, HELLO.

22:02.489 --> 22:04.791
MY MAN.
HOW'S IT GOING, BROTHER?

22:04.891 --> 22:06.993
- ( laughs ) PRETTY GOOD.
- GIVE ME SOME.

22:07.093 --> 22:10.262
ALL RIGHT.
WHAT, ARE YOU USING MY NAME
TO GET A TABLE IN HERE?

22:10.363 --> 22:12.565
WELL, IT'S SO CROWDED.
I JUST THOUGHT YOU'D...

22:12.665 --> 22:14.434
- REALLY?
- ...HAVE A BETTER CHANCE.

22:14.534 --> 22:16.503
- DID YOU? AH.
- YEAH.

22:16.603 --> 22:20.272
YOU WANT TO JOIN US?
YOU COULD EAT WITH US.

22:20.373 --> 22:22.041
- ARE YOU SURE? REALLY?
- PLEASE.

22:22.141 --> 22:24.377
- SIT DOWN.
- I MISS YOU.

22:24.477 --> 22:26.312
- YOU SURE?
- Both: YEAH, MM-HMM.

22:26.413 --> 22:28.314
- GREAT.
- OH, BY THE WAY,

22:28.415 --> 22:31.317
I PUT YOU UP
FOR AN N.A.A.C.P.
IMAGE AWARD.

22:31.418 --> 22:32.685
- YEAH YEAH.
- YOU DID?

22:32.785 --> 22:35.388
FINGERS CROSSED, BABY.
I THINK YOU'LL WIN.

22:35.488 --> 22:37.524
- OH, THANK YOU.
- HOW IS LORETTA?

22:37.624 --> 22:39.726
OH, SHE'S--
SHE'S-- YEAH.

22:39.826 --> 22:42.128
- YEAH?
- YEAH, SHE'S GOOD.

22:43.396 --> 22:45.297
HOW'S THE NO-FLY
UNDERWEAR GUY?

22:45.398 --> 22:48.401
UM, IT'S NOT HAPPENING.

22:48.501 --> 22:51.237
- IT DIDN'T WORK OUT.
- REALLY?

22:51.337 --> 22:55.608
- YEAH.
- MAYBE LARRY'S PEOPLE CAN
HOOK YOU UP WITH SOMEBODY.

22:55.708 --> 22:58.344
YOU KNOW LIL WAYNE?
YOU KNOW LIL WAYNE.

22:58.445 --> 23:00.246
OH, LIKE THIS.
YEAH.

23:00.346 --> 23:04.717
I CAN'T--
I CAN'T READ MY...

23:04.817 --> 23:06.486
- MENU.
- IT'S SO DARK IN HERE.

23:06.586 --> 23:08.287
- IT'S SO DARK.
I HONESTLY HAVE--
- UNBELIEVABLE.

23:08.387 --> 23:11.023
THIS IS INSANE.
HOW DO THEY EXPECT PEOPLE
TO READ THIS MENU?

23:11.123 --> 23:12.258
- HONESTLY?
- YOU CAN'T.

23:12.358 --> 23:13.726
I'VE GOT A CANDLE HERE
AND I CAN'T READ IT.

23:13.826 --> 23:15.895
- I'M GONNA GO OUTSIDE.
- OH YEAH, I'M GONNA GO OUTSIDE.

23:15.995 --> 23:19.031
- I'LL GO OUT WITH YOU.
- LARRY, WHAT YOU PUTTING
ON YOUR HAIR?

23:19.131 --> 23:20.366
- I LIKE THAT.
- POSNER.

23:20.467 --> 23:23.369
YOU LEARNING, LARRY.
HANG IN THERE, BABY.

23:23.470 --> 23:25.438
OH, LOOK,
THE CAESAR SALAD.

23:25.538 --> 23:27.840
- CAESAR SALAD.
- YOU USED TO GET THAT.

23:27.940 --> 23:30.677
- THAT'S VERY GOOD HERE.
- RIGHT. WITH THE 200 CROUTONS.

23:30.777 --> 23:33.412
A LOT OF CROUTONS.
THERE WERE A LOT OF CROUTONS.

23:33.513 --> 23:35.615
TON OF CROUTONS.

23:39.986 --> 23:41.921
I CAN'T BELIEVE I'M
SITTING HERE WITH YOU.

23:42.021 --> 23:42.722
- WEIRD.
- HUH?

23:42.822 --> 23:44.323
- IT'S WEIRD.
- IT'S CRAZY.

23:44.423 --> 23:47.093
- ISN'T IT?
- I REALLY MISS YOU.

23:49.629 --> 23:51.898
- I MISS YOU TOO.
- YOU DO?

23:51.998 --> 23:54.467
WELL... KIND OF.

23:56.068 --> 23:57.704
I MEAN, I DO, I DO.

23:57.804 --> 24:00.873
IT'S JUST WHAT WAS HAPPENING
WAS NOT WORKING FOR ME.

24:00.973 --> 24:03.543
- IT JUST WASN'T--
I DON'T KNOW.
- WHAT?

24:03.643 --> 24:06.646
IT GOT TO THIS PLACE
WHERE YOU WERE

24:06.746 --> 24:10.382
ALWAYS AT THE HOUSE AND YOU
DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING TO DO

24:10.483 --> 24:12.418
AND YOU--
IT WAS JUST DIFFERENT.

24:12.519 --> 24:14.754
LIKE WHEN YOU WERE
WORKING ON "SEINFELD,"

24:14.854 --> 24:18.691
YOU HAD A JOB AND YOU'D
GET UP AND YOU'D GO, LIKE,

24:18.791 --> 24:21.561
DO SOMETHING
WITH OTHER PEOPLE.

24:21.661 --> 24:23.830
- OKAY.
- AND THEN YOU'D COME HOME

24:23.930 --> 24:26.599
AND IT WAS LIKE THAT WAS
THE RIGHT AMOUNT OF LARRY.

24:26.699 --> 24:28.501
- THIS IS-- THAT WAS...
- I UNDERSTAND.

24:28.601 --> 24:30.036
- ...TOO MUCH.
- TOO MUCH LARRY, I GET THAT.

24:30.136 --> 24:32.639
OKAY, TOO MUCH LARRY.
WE CAN REDUCE LARRY

24:32.739 --> 24:34.907
IN HALF.
WE CAN REDUCE LARRY
TO A THIRD.

24:35.007 --> 24:37.143
WE CAN REDUCE LARRY
TO THREE HOURS A DAY.

24:37.243 --> 24:39.078
- THAT'S--
- HUH?

24:39.178 --> 24:40.580
SLIVERS OF LARRY
IS BETTER.

24:40.680 --> 24:42.448
I GET THAT.
LOOK, I UNDERSTAND.

24:42.549 --> 24:44.350
I'VE GOT 24-HOUR LARRY,
YOU THINK I LIKE IT?

24:44.450 --> 24:46.653
- ( giggling )
- ( cell phone ringing )

24:51.891 --> 24:54.594
- HELLO?
- LARRY, DR. SCHAFFER
JUST CALLED.

24:54.694 --> 24:56.729
HE'S ON HIS WAY OVER
TO THE HOUSE RIGHT NOW.

24:56.829 --> 24:58.598
HE'S GOT THE RESULTS
OF THE BIOPSY.

24:58.698 --> 25:00.933
- HE'S COMING OVER
TO THE HOUSE RIGHT NOW?
- UH-HUH.

25:01.033 --> 25:02.034
I'm on my way!

25:02.134 --> 25:04.103
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

25:04.203 --> 25:06.405
- UH, YEAH. I GOTTA GO.
- IS IT AN EMERGENCY?

25:06.505 --> 25:08.307
YEAH, I GOTTA GO.
I'LL TALK TO YOU.

25:08.407 --> 25:10.509
I GOTTA GO GET OUT
OF SOMETHING.

25:16.716 --> 25:19.686
- ( tires squeal )
- SHIT, DAMN IT!

25:38.270 --> 25:40.106
COME ON, SCHMOHAWK.

25:40.206 --> 25:42.274
( honks )

25:50.116 --> 25:51.283
( yelps )

25:51.383 --> 25:52.484
- ( bangs car )
- LARRY!

25:52.585 --> 25:54.854
- OH MY GOD.
- WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

25:54.954 --> 25:57.156
NEVER MIND.
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.
NOW CALL MARTY.

25:57.256 --> 25:58.357
- BAM BAM--
- CALL MARTY.

25:58.457 --> 25:59.859
- I'LL GO IN THE HOUSE--
- YOU'RE LYING!

25:59.959 --> 26:02.695
JUST TELL ME,
YOU LIED, RIGHT?
YOU LIED, JEFF ENJOYED.

26:02.795 --> 26:04.797
- DIRTY GOD--
- ( car alarm blaring )

26:04.897 --> 26:05.898
OH!

26:05.998 --> 26:07.834
- OH MY GOD!
- ( car starts )

26:07.934 --> 26:10.236
DON'T LOOK AT THEM, LARRY.
DON'T GET EYE CONTACT.

26:10.336 --> 26:12.571
- OH MY GOD.
- GO! GO! GO!

26:12.672 --> 26:14.674
- HOLY JESUS!
- NICE!

26:14.774 --> 26:16.008
- OH MY GOD.
- ONLY CALL MARTY.

26:16.108 --> 26:17.576
- WHAT? YEAH, I AM.
- CALL MARTY.

26:17.677 --> 26:19.145
- GET OUT OF THE WAY.
- NO!

26:19.245 --> 26:21.914
- I GOTTA GET IN THERE, BAM BAM.
- NO-- OW! CALL HIM.

26:22.014 --> 26:24.416
- GET YOUR CELL OUT.
- BAMMER, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

26:24.516 --> 26:25.985
TELL HIM JEFF SAID
I WAS IN THE TOP 10!

26:26.085 --> 26:27.353
- TELL HIM.
- ( police siren )

26:27.453 --> 26:28.587
STOP IT.
CALM DOWN.

26:28.688 --> 26:29.956
TELL MARTY
JEFF ENJOYED ME.

26:30.056 --> 26:31.958
YOU SHOULD NOT HAVE
LEFT THE HOUSE.

26:32.058 --> 26:34.360
FOLKS, WE HAD
A REPORT OF A BREAK-IN.
DID YOU SEE ANYTHING?

26:34.460 --> 26:37.229
OKAY, SHE'LL
GIVE YOU A STATEMENT.
I'VE GOTTA GET IN THE HOUSE.

26:37.329 --> 26:40.266
- I'LL TAKE YOUR STATEMENT NOW.
- NO, SHE CAN'T GIVE YOU
A STATEMENT.

26:40.366 --> 26:42.334
SHE'S NOT QUALIFIED
TO MAKE A STATEMENT.
SHE'S CRAZY.

26:42.434 --> 26:43.870
WHAT?!
NO, SHE'S NOT CRAZY.

26:43.970 --> 26:46.305
YEAH, AFTER WHAT SHE SAID
AT DINNER TONIGHT,
SHE'S CRAZY.

26:46.405 --> 26:50.810
- OH NO NO, SHE--
- I'M TAKING HER BACK
TO THE HOME.

26:50.910 --> 26:53.780
- I'M TAKING HER BACK.
- IF SHE CAN'T GIVE ONE, I'LL
NEED A STATEMENT FROM YOU.

26:53.880 --> 26:56.015
HAVE A GOOD NIGHT.
SIR, DID YOU SEE A VEHICLE?

26:56.115 --> 26:58.350
WAS IT INDIVIDUALS?
WHAT HAPPENED?

26:58.450 --> 27:00.386
WHAT EXACTLY DID YOU SEE?

27:03.122 --> 27:05.892
SIR, YOUR ATTENTION HERE,
SIR, IF YOU WOULD, PLEASE.

27:05.992 --> 27:08.027
ALL RIGHT, WELL, I SAW A GUY
JUMP OVER A HEDGE

27:08.127 --> 27:10.362
ACROSS THE STREET.
HE HAD A...

27:12.064 --> 27:14.667
OH, THE DOCTOR'S COMING.
LARRY.

27:14.767 --> 27:18.037
FOLKS, I WISH THAT I HAD
BETTER NEWS FOR YOU.

27:18.137 --> 27:21.407
THE BIOPSY CAME BACK
POSITIVE FOR CANCER.

27:22.675 --> 27:24.176
- NOW--
- OH, LARRY, LARRY!

27:24.276 --> 27:27.013
- MR. DAVID,
MR. DAVID, ARE YOU OKAY?
- OH MY GOODNESS, LARRY.

27:27.113 --> 27:28.981
- ARE YOU WITH ME?
- COME ON, LARRY, COME ON.

27:29.081 --> 27:30.883
OKAY, ALL RIGHT.

27:30.983 --> 27:32.985
- I KNOW THIS CAN BE
VERY UPSETTING.
- DR. SCHAFFER,

27:33.085 --> 27:34.787
- CAN I GO IN AND SEE HER?
- YES.

27:34.887 --> 27:37.724
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.
NOW...

27:37.824 --> 27:39.759
THIS IS REALLY WHERE
THE HARD WORK STARTS.

27:39.859 --> 27:42.528
SHE'S GONNA
NEED A LOT OF HELP.
THERE'S A LOT OF VITAMINS,

27:42.628 --> 27:44.864
A LOT OF MEDICINES
THAT SHE'S GONNA NEED.

27:44.964 --> 27:46.733
ORGANIC JUICES
THREE TIMES A DAY.

27:46.833 --> 27:51.237
I WOULD
KEEP THE HOUSE WARMER.
KEEP IT AT ABOUT 78Â°

27:51.337 --> 27:54.006
TO 82Â° MINIMUM.
THE WARMER THE BETTER, REALLY.

27:54.106 --> 27:56.008
THAT HELPS
WITH THE HEALING PROCESS.

27:56.108 --> 27:59.645
I KNOW THIS IS
A LOT TO TAKE IN,
BUT IF YOU GUYS WORK HARD,

27:59.746 --> 28:03.682
ESPECIALLY YOU, IN TWO,
THREE, MAYBE FOUR YEARS,
SHE'S HOPEFULLY GONNA BE FINE.

28:03.783 --> 28:06.218
- DID YOU SAY FOUR YEARS?
- COULD BE, YEAH.

28:06.318 --> 28:09.121
AND YOUR LIFE IS MOSTLY GOING
TO BE TAKING HER TO APPOINTMENTS

28:09.221 --> 28:10.522
OR HERE WITH HER
IN THE HOUSE.

28:10.622 --> 28:12.091
I-I CAN STILL
PLAY GOLF.

28:12.191 --> 28:14.794
ABSOLUTELY NOT.
I DON'T IMAGINE
YOU'D HAVE TIME FOR THAT.

28:14.894 --> 28:16.963
- ONCE A WEEK?
- NO TIMES A WEEK.

28:17.063 --> 28:19.531
- YOU WON'T HAVE TIME FOR THAT.
- WHAT? NINE HOLES.

28:19.631 --> 28:22.368
ZERO HOLES, MR. DAVID!
THIS IS SERIOUS.

28:22.468 --> 28:25.371
NOW I WON'T LIE--
THINGS ARE GOING TO GET UGLY.

28:25.471 --> 28:28.107
THERE'S GOING TO BE VOMITING.
THERE'S GOING TO BE
INCONTINENCE,

28:28.207 --> 28:30.042
DEPRESSION,
UNSIGHTLY HAIR LOSS,

28:30.142 --> 28:32.178
WEIGHT LOSS.
SHE'LL BE IRRITABLE.

28:32.278 --> 28:35.047
LOTS OF MASSIVE MOOD SWINGS.
SHE COULD GET VIOLENT.

28:35.147 --> 28:37.249
HYSTERIA,
INCONTINENCE--

28:37.349 --> 28:38.818
